## NLP Parser Examples

```python
from scripts.analysis.ai_parser import parse_claim

# Example 1: multi-filter query
parse_claim("Babar in the 1st innings at MCG against Left-arm Pace")
# → {
#   "filters": {
#     "innings": 1,
#     "venue_name": "Melbourne Cricket Ground",
#     "bowler_hand": "Left",
#     "bowler_type": "Pace"
#   }
# }

# Example 2: bowling economy
parse_claim("Bumrah economy in Death overs in Tests since 2020")
# → {
#   "metric": "Economy Rate",
#   "filters": {
#     "match_phase": "Death",
#     "format": "Test",
#     "season": "2020"
#   }
# }
```

---

## Calculation Logic

### Batting
```
Batting Average  = total_runs / dismissals
Strike Rate      = (total_runs / balls_faced) × 100
Dot Ball %       = (balls with 0 runs) / balls × 100
Boundary %       = (balls scoring 4 or 6) / balls × 100
High Score       = max(innings_runs per match_id+innings group)
Milestones       = count(innings_runs ≥ 50) or count(innings_runs ≥ 100)
```

### Bowling
```
Economy Rate        = runs_conceded / (balls_bowled / 6)
Bowling Average     = runs_conceded / wickets
Bowling Strike Rate = balls_bowled / wickets
Dots Forced         = count(deliveries where runs_total == 0)
Extras Conceded     = sum(wides + noballs + byes + legbyes)
```

---

## Dataset Column Requirements

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The filter engine checks whether each column exists before applying that filter,
> so partial schemas degrade gracefully. For full 38-parameter support, the
> [matches.csv](file:///d:/University/Semester%208th/FYP/AI/matches.csv) should include these columns:

| Column | Source | Used By |
|--------|--------|---------|
| `venue_name` | ingestion engine | Filter #1 |
| [city](file:///d:/University/Semester%208th/FYP/AI/scripts/analysis/validate_model.py#65-67) | ingestion engine | Filter #2, #3 |
| `match_type` | ingestion engine | Filter #4 |
| [date](file:///d:/University/Semester%208th/FYP/AI/scripts/analysis/validate_model.py#459-580) | ingestion engine | Filter #5 |
| `day_night` | raw JSON `info.match_type_variant` | Filter #6 |
| `toss_winner`, `toss_decision` | raw JSON `info.toss` | Filter #7, #8 |
| `innings` | delivery loop | Filter #9 |
| `competition` | raw JSON `info.competition` | Filter #10 |
| `home_team` | raw JSON teams[0] | Filter #11 |
| `neutral_venue` | raw JSON `info.neutral_venue` | Filter #12 |
| `wicket_type` | delivery wickets | Filter #18 |
| `batting_position` | inferred from batter order | Filter #21 |
| `non_striker` | raw delivery | Filter #22 |
| `over` | raw delivery | Filter #34, #35 |
| `runs_batter`, `is_wicket`, `is_bowler_wicket`, `runs_total` | existing | Metrics |

> [!NOTE]
> Currently [matches.csv](file:///d:/University/Semester%208th/FYP/AI/matches.csv) only has 12 columns. Filters for columns that don't
> exist are skipped silently — the engine still computes any metric that **is**
> available (e.g. batting average with country/format/innings/opponent_type filters).

---

## Running the System

```powershell
# Full claim validation (uses LLM if GEMINI_API_KEY is set):
python scripts/analysis/validate_model.py "Virat Kohli averages 55 in Tests in England"

# Override with a specific claim:
python scripts/analysis/validate_model.py "Babar Azam has 45 average in 1st innings"

# Parser unit tests (no DB or CSV needed):
python scripts/analysis/test_parser_quick.py
```

---

## Filter Application Data-Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Claim String
    participant P as ai_parser
    participant IE as IdentityEngine
    participant DF as matches.csv (DataFrame)
    participant V as validate_model

    C->>P: parse_claim()
    P-->>V: {subject, metric, claimed_value, filters[38]}
    V->>IE: resolve_for_ingestion(subject)
    IE-->>V: canonical_name
    V->>DF: read_csv (matches.csv)
    DF-->>V: raw deliveries
    V->>V: df[df['batter'] == canonical]  (subject pre-filter)
    V->>V: apply_filters(df, filters, engine, is_batting)
    Note over V: Applies up to 38 filters sequentially<br/>Skips filters for missing columns
    V->>V: _batting_metrics() or _bowling_metrics()
    V-->>C: Verdict + accuracy %
```
